                                        Community building, e.g., Reddit, Twitter, Stack Overflow, Discord
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                            </div>
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </DocsPageSection>
                

                <DocsPageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="Where does the money go?">
                        <Description>
                            All funds are going to <CodeInline>Gardnet AB</CodeInline> which is a Swedish company owned by <MudLink Href="https://github.com/Garderoben">Garderoben</MudLink>, the creator of MudBlazor.<br/><br/>
                            <CodeInline>Gardnet AB</CodeInline> is using the funds to:
                            <div class="d-flex flex-column px-2">
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Secure MudBlazor's future as the best choice out there.
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Cover expenses related to development of MudBlazor, e.g., domain names, certificates, hosting and licenses.
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                            </div>
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </DocsPageSection>

                <DocsPageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="What's the difference between GitHub and OpenCollective?">
                        <Description>
                            Funds received via <b>GitHub</b>, directly go to <CodeInline>Gardnet AB</CodeInline> and the core team's mission. The company is a profit entity with one goal, to secure MudBlazor's future.<br/><br/>
                            Funds received via <b>Open Collective</b> are managed transparently and aimed to sustain MudBlazor and its needs.<br/>
                            As a <MudTooltip Color="Color.Dark" Placement="Placement.Top">
                                     <ChildContent>
                                         <MudText Class="docs-text-dec">Fiscal Host</MudText>
                                     </ChildContent>
                                     <TooltipContent>
                                         A Fiscal Host is an entity that holds the money on<br/>
                                         behalf of a Collective and takes care of<br/>
                                         accounting, taxes, and invoices.
                                     </TooltipContent>
                                 </MudTooltip>, all funds are kept there until we submit an expense.
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </DocsPageSection>

